ACTUS IV.—so. 1.

Sos'rnau, wife of Chremes, enters in great excitament at having found the ring, with which she had exposed her daughter, in time past. Her story is confirmed by the nurse. She unfolds to Chremes how she hed disobeyed his orders when it was exposed, and had given the old Corinthian woman to whom the babe had been consigned, to be made away with, a ring to place with it. This ring she has found in possession of Antiphila. Chremes after awhile forgiven her, and goes with her to see his new found daughter.
